<tr class="bg0"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a  href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/Gladiator/int_2dbc8492'>Film: Gladiator / int_2dbc8492</a></td>
<td><div title='http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment'>comment</div></td>
<td><i>Doomed Moral Victor: Maximus becomes a darling of the public, kills the emperor in a duel and dies afterwards. He was already mortally wounded by the Emperor just before they entered the arena. It was meant to be more of a fancy execution than a duel, in order to discredit the hero and bolster the strength of the Emperor. The evil Emperor still loses.</i></td>
</tr>


