<td><i>We All Die Someday: Maximus tells Commodus that a late friend once told him &quot;Death smiles at us all. All we can do is smile back.&quot; Commodus wonders whether the friend did the same thing at his own death. Maximus replies that Commodus should know, since that friend was Marcus Aurelius, Commodus' father.</i></td>
