<tr class="bg0"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a  href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/Gladiator/int_b03b10fb'>Film: Gladiator / int_b03b10fb</a></td>
<td><div title='http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment'>comment</div></td>
<td><i>Aluminum Christmas Trees: Commodus deciding to fight a gladiator in the arena looks like a plot device to let Maximus get his revenge. The historical Commodus did actually fight in gladiator contests, although it isn't how he died. The writers planned to have a scene with popular gladiators endorsing products, which happened historically, but it was decided that audiences would think it was unrealistic.</i></td>
</tr>


