<tr class="bg1"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a name='int_e55b793' href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/Gladiator/int_e55b793'>Film: Gladiator / int_e55b793</a></td>
<td><div title='http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type'>type</div></td>
<td><a href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Main/WordOfGod'>This entry is trivia, which is cool and all, but not a trope. On a work, it goes on the Trivia tab. Word of God</a></td>
</tr>


<tr class="bg0"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a  href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/Gladiator/int_e55b793'>Film: Gladiator / int_e55b793</a></td>
<td><div title='http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment'>comment</div></td>
<td><i>At one point, Rome is described as being founded as a Republic, and numerous characters refer to plans to turn it back into a republic for the people. Rome was actually founded as a kingdom, only becoming a republic later on. Word of God is that Roman history was not re-written for the film, but that these statements were incorrect within the film itself, reflecting how the characters themselves preferred to see history.</i></td>
</tr>


<tr class="bg1"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a  href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/Gladiator/int_e55b793'>Film: Gladiator / int_e55b793</a></td>
<td><div title='http://skipforward.net/skipforward/resource/seeder/skipinions/featureApplicability'>featureApplicability</div></td>
<td><i>1.0</i></td>
