<tr class="bg0"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a  href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/Gladiator/int_ff4e42a4'>Film: Gladiator / int_ff4e42a4</a></td>
<td><div title='http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment'>comment</div></td>
<td><i>Hollywood Tactics: Flaming arrows are used in the opening battle, although it appears that they are used mainly for their psychological effect Any Roman legion breaking ranks during a battle as shown in the film would have been decimated; Roman soldiers were taught to fight as part of a shield-wall and given very little individual combat training. In a loose melee as depicted in the battle, the barbarians would have had the upper hand.</i></td>
</tr>


